        "icon": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/shsm/AGYqVK3_qtrkGe-n6KHvH5jOin8CnUYVK50DLVR5kS0UuRVwGW9zOoBwidESd4CLcNKOsmMHRQ=w40-h40-c0x00000000-cc"
      },
      {
        "title": "The 11600K CPU I got was actually a very weak one. I overclocked it to 5.0ghz, but its voltage ca...",
        "text": "The 11600K CPU I got was actually a very weak one. I overclocked it to 5.0ghz, but its voltage came up to a staggering 1.48V, which is very unusual in past generations of cpus such as Gen 9 or gen 10 (10600K is about 1.35V and can be overclocked to 5.0ghz But 10600k can be overclocked to 5.1 or even 5.2) if you are a person who wants to overclocked and use this CPU with full core you have to be prepared for it to have very exaggerated voltage and power consumption. I used full core 5.0 and played with bf5. Power consumption was 130w at 2k resolution and temperature was 76 degrees and heat sink was msi 280R has an average power consumption of 180W in FPU( disabled AVX512) which is an amazing temperature core power consumption compared to 10600K(10600k in all core5.0ghz almost 140w) In general, if you happen to have a nice radiator and you don't care about temperature and voltage you can buy 11600K or 11700K or if you care about single-core performance 11600K is a good choice but if you are a player who likes extreme temperature it is recommended to buy a 10th generation CPU Or wait for generation 12 cpus",
